Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium high heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @korma curry paste{50%g} and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @water{75%ml} and @chicken stock powder{1} and stir well to combine. Add the @cooked pulled chicken{200%g} and chickpeas, stir and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened and everything is piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time, stirring, until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. While the spinach is wilting, heat the @steamed basmati rice{1%200g pack} according to pack instructions.

When everything is ready, stir the @mango chutney{40%g} through the curry. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if it needs it.

Divide the rice between plates and top with the curry. Enjoy!